"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-04-paris-2024-olympics-dtigress-beats-canada-79-70-zooms-into-semis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's D'Tigress sealed a place in the quarter-finals of the women's basketball event at the 2024 Olympic Games on Sunday.  The West Africans defeated Canada 79-70 in their last group game.  Rena Wakama's side started the game on the front foot and had a 10-point lead at some point but allowed the Canadians back into the game.    The two teams could not be separated at the end of the first quarter, sharing spoils 18-18.  D'Tigress went into the break still very much in the game, trailing their opponents by only four points (41-37).  The African champions rallied in the third quarter to lead 55-46.  Nigeria won 79-70 at the end of the game.          Preseason: Why Chelsea lost 4-2 to Man City - Maresca  Gafar joins Plateau United from Morak FC  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  FIBA WWQ 2026: Gallant D'Tigress fall 77-60 to Korea  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"